<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1100,1413]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,619,1135,1160]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">
Condition of the 
<typeStatus box="[413,477,1135,1160]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">types</typeStatus>
. 
<typeStatus box="[493,613,1135,1160]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">Lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Perfect condition. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[844,1027,1135,1160]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">
<typeStatus box="[844,1022,1135,1160]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">Paralectotypes</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Specimens collected by Hetschko: wings somewhat rubbed, antennae soiled with what appears to be fungal hyphae, one of them with both antennae missing. Specimen identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[531,777,1207,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera" genus="Myrmecopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polistes">
<emphasis box="[531,777,1207,1232]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">Myrmecopsis polistes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Rebel with the abdomen kept in a gelatin vial. Last 
<typeStatus box="[151,302,1244,1269]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">paralectotype</typeStatus>
with right forewing slightly wrinkled, otherwise in good condition.
</paragraph>
