<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="519" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1100,1413]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1279,1304]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from the eight specimens mentioned above. It was revalidated from its synonymy under 
<taxonomicName authority="Dyar, 1910" authorityName="Dyar" authorityYear="1910" box="[356,780,1316,1341]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanogen">
<emphasis box="[356,637,1316,1341]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">Pseudosphex melanogen</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dyar" box="[649,780,1316,1341]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" refString="Dyar, H. G. (1910) Descriptions of some new species and genera of Lepidoptera from Mexico. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 38, 229 - 273. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.38 - 1742.229" type="journal article" year="1910">
Dyar, 
<number box="[724,780,1316,1340]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" value="1910.0">1910</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[832,1166,1316,1341]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" refString="Simmons, R. B. &amp; Weller, S. J. (2006) Review of the Sphecosoma genus group using adult morphology (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Thomas Say Publications in Entomology: Monographs. Published by the Entomological Society of America, Lanham, Maryland, 108 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Simmons and Weller (
<number box="[1097,1158,1316,1341]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who also placed both species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Newman, 1850" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1850" box="[269,603,1351,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera" genus="Myrmecopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[269,418,1353,1376]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">Myrmecopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Newman" box="[427,603,1351,1376]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" refString="Newman, E. (1850) Description of an apparently new lepidopteran insect, of the Family Glaucopidae, from the Upper Amazons. Zoologist, 8, 112 - 123." type="journal article" year="1850">
Newman, 
<number box="[543,603,1351,1376]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" value="1850.0">1850</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[614,934,1351,1376]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" refString="Simmons, R. B. &amp; Weller, S. J. (2006) Review of the Sphecosoma genus group using adult morphology (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Thomas Say Publications in Entomology: Monographs. Published by the Entomological Society of America, Lanham, Maryland, 108 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Simmons and Weller (
<number box="[867,926,1351,1376]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
resurrected this genus to encompass several species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, 1818" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1818" box="[473,782,1388,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[473,619,1388,1413]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">Pseudosphex</emphasis>
Hübner, 
<number box="[723,782,1388,1412]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" value="1818.0">1818</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
